I"Q<h2 id="prerequisites-for-adding-products">Prerequisites for adding products:</h2>

<p>You need a valid Priority Account.</p>

<h2 id="steps-to-add-products-in-priority">Steps to Add Products in Priority:</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Login to the Priority Portal with valid credentials.</li>
  <li>Navigate to the menu and click on the Inventory button.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/staticfiles/connectors/media/application-connector/AddProduct-Priority1.png" alt="AddProduct-Priority1" /></p>
<ol>
  <li>Click on the option Part Catalogue &gt; Part Catalogue from the sub-menus.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/staticfiles/connectors/media/application-connector/AddProduct-Priority2.png" alt="AddProduct-Priority2" /></p>

<ol>
  <li>The Part Catalogue window opens up. Enter the Part Number and the Description.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/staticfiles/connectors/media/application-connector/AddProduct-Priority3.png" alt="AddProduct-Priority3" /></p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> The Part Number and the Description needs to be unique every-time a new product is registered.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Once the Part Number and the Description is provided, enter the Product Details, Additional Details, and the Prices and cost. These 
field can be accessible by clicking on the menu as shown below.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/staticfiles/connectors/media/application-connector/AddProduct-Priority4.png" alt="AddProduct-Priority4" /></p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> The Wholesale Price (under prices and costs) is needed to be provided, else the item price will not sync.</p>

<p><img src="/staticfiles/connectors/media/application-connector/AddProduct-Priority5.png" alt="AddProduct-Priority5" /></p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> For providing Item Variants,The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Ecommerce Attribute</code> is needed to be clicked in the subform (lower section of the form)</p>
:ET